# Build context hygiene. Anything listed here NEVER ends up in the
# Docker image, even if a misbehaving COPY tries to grab it.
#
# Two reasons we're aggressive:
# 1. Secrets: .env, *.pem, broker creds, etc. -- absolutely must not
#    leak into a layer (image layers are world-readable to anyone with
#    pull access).
# 2. Size: SQLite DBs, model artefacts, and the venv balloon the build
#    context to ~1 GB if we let them in. That's 10x slower to send to
#    the daemon for every build.

# --- Secrets ---------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
secrets/

# --- VCS ------------------------------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/

# --- Python tooling -------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
*.egg
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
.tox/

# --- Virtual envs (we reinstall inside the image) ------------------------
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/
.python-version

# --- Runtime data (volume-mounted, NOT baked in) -------------------------
data/
logs/
reports/
models/
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.joblib
*.pkl
*.pt
*.pth
*.h5
artifacts/

# --- IDE / OS cruft ------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
.cursor/
*.swp
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# --- Docs that don't belong in the image --------------------------------
*.md
!README.md
docs/

# --- Tests (we run them in CI, not in the prod image) -------------------
tests/
